h3. Summary

When using {{AP.getCurrentUser}} inside a {{serviceDeskPortalRequestCreatePropertyPanels}} module, the function returns an empty {} object. In comparison, the same code works for generalPages and webPanels.

*Steps to replicate*
# In your connect app, add module:
{code}
"serviceDeskPortalRequestCreatePropertyPanels": [
      {
          "key": "customer-portal-property-panel",
          "url": "/customer-portal/request?requestTypeId{servicedesk.requestTypeId}&serviceDeskId={servicedesk.serviceDeskId}"
      }
    ]
{code}
# Open create-request view on customer portal to load above mentioned panel.
# When panel is loaded, open web-browser console and type:
{code}
AP.user.getCurrentUser(function(user) {
  console.log("The Atlassian Account ID is", user.atlassianAccountId);
});
{code}

h3. Notes

Issue started 16 Oct

Situation:
# The reporter opens an issue with approvals;
# The reporter select himself as an approver;
# The reporter approver his own issue.

Expected:
# The reporter opens an issue with approvals;
# The reporter select himself as an approver, but he can't see himself in the list since his name is already in the "reporter field";
OR
# The reporter select himself as an approver;
# The reporter try to approve himself but receives and error saying that he can't approve since he is the reporter.
